vGRF was collected by two force platforms embedded in the instrumented treadmill (sampling at 1,000 Hz). According to a previous study21, a fourth-order zero-lag low-pass Butterworth filter with a cut-off frequency at 25 Hz was used to filter the vGRFs. Further, a 40-N threshold for further vGRF analysis was used22–25. Using the vGRF, the values of factual, tc, and Fpeak in both the unaffected and affected limbs were determined. The representative value of stiffness was determined by averaging five consecutive steps that were within 3% of the target fstep. The kleg (N/m) was computed as the ratio of Fpeak to ΔL at the midstance. Thus,1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
